headline: MSCI’s (NYSE:MSCI) Q4 CY2025 Earnings Results: Revenue In Line With Expectations
summary: Investment analytics provider MSCI (NYSE:MSCI) met Wall Streets revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 10.6% year on year to $822.5 million. Its non-GAAP profit of $4.66 per share was 1.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: MSCI: Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: On a per-share basis, the New York-based company said it had profit of $3.81. Earnings, adjusted for pretax expenses and amortization costs, came to $4.66 per share. The results surpassed Wall Street expectations.
